This product is a Go port of the Pi coding agent originally written in
TypeScript by Mario Zechner and the upstream Pi contributors:

    https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono
    Copyright (c) 2025 Mario Zechner
    Licensed under the MIT License.

The upstream MIT license notice is retained in LICENSE. Significant portions
of the architecture, protocols, on-disk session format, and tool semantics
are derived from that upstream work. Behavioural compatibility is tracked in
docs/TS_COMPATIBILITY.md.

The TypeScript/JavaScript extension samples under examples/extensions/ are
carried over from the upstream Pi project (MIT) and are provided for reference.
pi-go ships a minimal Node-based script bridge that can execute simple custom
tool extensions, but it does not yet implement the full upstream extension API,
so most of these samples will not run end to end. The examples/extensions/doom-overlay demo
integrates DOOM via doomgeneric (https://github.com/ozkl/doomgeneric) and id
Software's DOOM source, which are licensed under GPL-2.0. No compiled DOOM
artifacts are distributed in this repository; they are built locally from
GPL-2.0 sources and are not covered by this project's MIT license.

